  "excerpt": "PlayStation's special-edition DualSense Controller themed around The Last of Us releases April 10, three days before Season 2 premieres on HBO.",
  "siteName": "GameSpot",
  "favicon": "https://www.gamespot.com/a/bundles/gamespotsite/images/touch-icon-ipad-retina-precomposed.png",
  "text": "GameSpot may receive revenue from affiliate and advertising partnerships for sharing this content and from purchases through links. After selling out almost instantly when preorders opened on March 14, The Last of Us Limited Edition DualSense Controller is back in stock at two major retailers. As of March 17 at 2 PM PT, Target and Best Buy are taking preorders again, but the special-edition PS5 controller remains out of stock at Amazon and Walmart. It appears that the bulk of the stock will be sold by PlayStation itself, as the controller is still available to order at PS Direct despite being such a hot commodity at major retailers. The Last of Us-themed DualSense Controller releases April 10, three days before Season 2 of the TV adaptation airs on HBO.The Last of Us DualSense Controller Preorders:Target - In stockPlayStation Direct - In stockBest Buy - In stockWalmart - Sold outGameStop - In stock | Pro members onlyAmazon - Sold out The Last Of Us Limited Edition DualSense Controller $85 | Releases April 10 Designed with a black and white color scheme, the controller is adorned with various icons and emblems representing different events and characters from the game. The bottom half of the controller (including both analog sticks) is a brilliant white, while the top half (including the face buttons and D-pad) is black. You’ll get a pop of white on the triggers and on \"The Last of Us\" text emblazoned on its back. Fans will also notice several easter eggs scattered around the gamepad's surface, including a firefly, moth, and wolf printed on the controller, referencing the Fireflles organization and the characters Ellie and Abby.It’s a good-looking controller by all accounts, and it’s bound to be just as popular as previous limited-edition models from PlayStation. Sony has released several other limited-edition DualSense controllers, including version based on Astro Bot, Spider-Man, God of War, Concord, and more. While most of these are sold out, you can still grab the official Helldivers 2 DualSense and Fortnite DualSense controllers for $85 each. Like the new Last of Us controller, these gamepads feature unique color schemes and decals themed after the games they're based on.More Limited-Edition DualSense ControllersDualSense Controller - Fortnite Edition -- $85 See at AmazonSee at TargetSee at PlayStation DirectSee at Best BuyDualSense Controller - Helldivers 2 Edition -- $85 | Exclusive to PlayStation DirectThe Last of Us CollectiblesThe Last of Us Season 1 - Limited Edition Steelbook (4K Blu-ray) If you want to refresh your memory ahead of the premiere of The Last of Us Season 2, check out the brand-new Limited Edition Steelbook release of Season 1 on 4K Blu-ray. The new edition comes with a very cool steelbook case and is on sale for $38 (was $50) at Amazon. You could display your steelbook case next to the official action figure versions of Joel \u0026 Ellie, who joined the PlayStation Shapes collectible lineup last fall. The two-pack of articulated and customizable action figures is discounted to $40 (was $50). And if you like board games, The Last of Us was recently adapted into a cooperative strategy game called Escape the Dark. Designed to be played solo or alongside up to four friends, the officially licensed tabletop game is available for $71.49 at Amazon.The Last of Us Season 1 Limited Edition Steelbook (4K) -- $38 ($50) | Releases March 18The Last of Us: Joel \u0026 Ellie Action Figure Pack -- $40 ($50)The Last of Us: Escape the Dark Board Game -- $71.49 ($75)The Last of Us Game DealsIf haven't played video game series yet or are looking to add physical copies to your PS5 collection, you can grab The Last of Us Part 1 for $50 (was $70) and The Last of Us Part 2 Remastered for $50. Meanwhile, GameSpot sister site Fanatical is offering a steep discount on The Last of Us Part 1 for PC and a 10% preorder discount for The Last of Us Part 2 Remastered ahead of the PC port's April 3 launch.The Last of Us PS5 Physical Editions:The Last of Us Part 1 (PS5) -- $49.49 ($70)The Last of Us Part 2 Remastered (PS5) -- $50The Last of Us PC Game Deals:The Last of Us Part 1 -- $27 ($60)The Last of Us Part 1 Digital Deluxe -- $31.49 ($70)The Last of Us Part 2 Remastered -- $45 ($50) | Releases April 3Disclosure: GameSpot and Fanatical are both owned by Fandom. The Last Of Us Limited-Edition PS5 Controller Preorders Restocked At Major Retailers Final Fantasy Anniversary Collection Drops To Best Price Yet At Amazon PlayStation PC Games Are Over 50% Off At Fanatical, Cheaper Than Steam Spring Sale + Show More More Gaming, Tech, and Entertainment Deals \u0026 Preorders Links (5) The Hobbit \u0026 The Silmarillion Tolkien Illustrated Special Editions Get $100-Plus Discounts The Boy And The Heron Steelbook: Studio Ghibli's Only 4K Blu-Ray On Sale For Best-Ever Price Stephen King's The Stand Hardcover Edition Drops To Lowest Price In Years Astro Bot PS5 Slim Bundles Are Available Now - $50 Cheaper Than PS5 On Its Own Berserk Deluxe Edition Manga Steeply Discounted Ahead Of Volume 42's Release Next Week There are currently no available deals GameSpot may get a commission from retail offers. Got a news tip or want to contact us directly? Email news@gamespot.com",
